The paper discusses meta-learning methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. The focus of the paper is on Model-Agnostic Meta-Learning (MAML), which is a popular meta-learning algorithm used for adapting to new tasks quickly. The paper also discusses deep models and their importance in the success of MAML. Given these topics, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
